    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>County Posting Data On Heating Oil Prices</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Westchester County, NY, posts on its Web site heating oil prices from more than 75 companies, which range from $1.25 to $1.70 a gallon; photo (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>With the cost of heating oil rising, the county is posting price information from more than 75 companies on its Web site at www.westchestergov.com.</p>
        <p>In a survey, prices ranged from $1.25 to $1.70 a gallon, which amounts to a difference of $450 over the heating season for a typical consumer who might use 1,000 gallons. The lowest price in the survey, $1.25 a gallon, was posted by Edgewood Oil of Yonkers.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>With the cost of heating oil rising, the county is posting price information from more than 75 companies on its Web site at www.westchestergov.com.</p>
        <p>In a survey, prices ranged from $1.25 to $1.70 a gallon, which amounts to a difference of $450 over the heating season for a typical consumer who might use 1,000 gallons. The lowest price in the survey, $1.25 a gallon, was posted by Edgewood Oil of Yonkers.</p>
        <p>Included in the survey is information on service contracts, discounts for cash, discounts for the elderly, automatic delivery and 24-hour service as well as explanations of these terms.</p>
        <p>The Web site is similar to one the county started in June listing gasoline prices at about 400 gas stations.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
        <p>IN BUSINESS</p>
      </block>
